-- S&P downgrades Generali and other Italian insurers
-- 
-- Fri Dec 12, 2014 12:22PM EST
-- None



MILAN, Dec 12 (Reuters) - Rating agency Standand & Poor's said on Friday it had cut by one notch its long-term ratings on Assicurazioni Generali <GASI.MI> and other three Italian insurers following the downgrade of the country's sovereign rating.

In a statement, S&P said it now rated Generali 'BBB+' from 'A-'. UnipolSai <US.MI> and Cattolica <CASS.MI> 'BBB-' from 'BBB'. The Italian unit of German insurer Allianz was downgraded to 'A-' from 'A', it said.